On the 43rd anniversary of the Supreme Court ruling in Roe v. Wade, President Obama released a statement affirming a woman's freedom to make her own choices about her body and health. He emphasized the importance of the government not interfering in private decisions between a woman and her doctor. The President also reiterated his commitment to protecting constitutional rights, including a woman's access to affordable healthcare and reproductive freedom. He concluded by stating that every individual in America deserves the rights, freedoms, and opportunities to pursue their dreams.